title: KEISHA JACKSON DISCOGRAPHY
description:
For those of you who don't know this great singer, who by the way did NOT receive enough attention for her great singing voice and two slammin' albums,... she is the daughter of the great and RAUNCHY MILLIE JACKSON. Yes Millie Jackson...you remember her as the woman who made those BLUE LIGHT albums that only your parents listened to and you dared not touch even so much as the album cover. Lol

Ms. Keisha Jackson made two incredible albums during her musical career and now does mostly behind the scenes work. Her MATURE LOVE track did very well using the NEW JACK SOUND of the 90s and a slick video that put Ms. Jackson on the map (You can look on YouTube for the video of MATURE LOVE from Keisha to see what I mean). The rest of the album was well produced and there is not one track that is not absolutely likeable. Listen adn hear for yourself and have that flashback of how good the early nineties were given the fashion, haircuts, dances and good times...

Here is the discography of Keisha Jackson. I would suggest listening to the 1991 album first, it is hits from front to back and please remember to seed seed seed to keep the music alive and above all enjoy and share those artists/music that you may have that is not on TPB.
